<br>
That was a nifty little quest you posted to the mailing list Warnie. I can see this being quite common and very fun indeed.<br>
One thing we will need to be careful of is - if there is a single prize there should probably be a way to let other know that person XYZ is already attempting the quest. This would just save another person heading off to do it - spending up big or whatever then arriving to collect their reward only to find they finished second <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
We could alleviate this by using this message board (or the events/quests one maybe) to offer quests - that way people who are attempting it can let others know through there.<br>
The other way is to have a multiple reward option - which is much harder for individuals to sponsor...<br>
<br>
good work anyhow Warnie!<br>
<br>
For those that missed it here is Warnie's little quest:<br>
=================================================<br>
The Quest:  Head to Halas.  Purchase a few bags and fill them with the molds for every piece of large banded armour.  Return the bags with the molds to Warnin.  This may take some research to find out where they are and how much they cost.<br>
 <br>
The Reward:  Polished Granite Tomahawk.  It is worth around 125pp, a bit more than actually buying a full suite of banded.   PGT is a 1hs 6/26 magic weapon with the effect of Berserk Strength.  It can be used by all races, and these classes:  Warrior, Paladin, Rogue, Shadow Knight, Ranger, Bard, and Shaman.<br>
========================================<br>
